## 🔐 Security & Production Notes

| Concern | Mitigation |
|---------|------------|
| **PAT Exposure** | Store `GITHUB_PAT` in Secrets Manager (AWS SSM, HashiCorp Vault). Never commit to `.env`. Rotate quarterly. |
| **Idempotency Loss** | Always use Redis. In-memory cache resets on container restart, causing duplicate GitHub dispatches. |
| **GitHub Rate Limits** | `repository_dispatch` consumes `1 request/trigger`. Well within limits. Queue bursts if >50 events/sec. |
| **Payload Sanitization** | Microservice only forwards `job_id`, `project_id`, `error`, and `artifacts`. Strips internal `worker_node`, `stack_trace_id`, etc. |
| **Failure Handling** | Returns `200` to AethelFrame on handler errors to prevent infinite retries. Logs to stdout/stderr for DLQ parsing. |
| **TLS Termination** | Deploy behind a reverse proxy (Nginx, Cloudflare) with enforced HTTPS webhook URLs. |

